A network of brain regions that are active when not focused on the outside
world and the brain is at wakeful rest.  Consists of:
- Medial Temporal Lobe (memory)
- Medial Prefrontal Cortex (theory of mind)
- Posterior Cingulate Cortex (integration)
- Ventral Precuneus
- Medial, Lateral and Inferior Parietal Cortex
| http://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Default_mode_network&oldid=617149142

